If you want Proot's sunflare as well, here's how to get it. It only takes a couple of minutes. Unity Assets Explorer works just fine in Linux through Wine, so these instructions work for Linux too:

1. Make a backup copy of KSP_Data\sharedassets9.assets

2. Download Unity Assets Explorer and extract it to a folder

3. Extract the sharedassets9.assets file from the KSPRC download to a folder somewhere

4. Run Unity Assets Explorer. Click on "Open Assets-file" and navigate to the sharedassets9.assets file from KSPRC

5. Select "sun_flare.tex". Right click and choose "Extract This File"

6. Click on "Open Assets-file" again and navigate to KSP's assets file: KSP_Data\sharedassets9.assets

7. Select "sun_flare.tex". Right click and choose "Import This File from DDS"

8. Click "Save as Assets-file". Name it "sharedassets9.assets" and overwrite the original file when prompted (you did make a backup, right?)

9. Enjoy Proot's sunflare.

What mods do you have installed? I'm not sure I can specifically help you, but whoever does would probably like to know.

As I already said I fixed it by deleting all the unnecessary configs from GameData/BoulderCo/Clouds.

You have to leave only one of them or you will get multiple clouds.

I have TextureReplacer, PlanetShine and so on (everything which was required for KSPRC, latests versions).

I didn't replace the stock assets file (it would break stuff until updated) and RSS configs and etc of mods which I don't have.

I also added -force-opengl flag to my game executable and my game with >40 mods eats less 2gb of ram (or a bit more).

I myself seem to have some success with this. I have several other mods, but seem to be pretty stable. The heat warning bar being the only real danger for crashing.

I do have a very slow memory leak. I can play for about 1-2 hours. My game will start at about 2.6GB and slowly increase over time. I have infernal robotics, chatter, KSPRC and the updated parts of KSPRC. As well I have the life support mod and the realSolarsystem mod. Not sure what is causing the leak, as I'm not too oriented with the debug system in KSP, but I am having a blast.

Once KSPRC is updated, I will likely rebuild my mods, and hopefully by then squad will fix the heat warning memory leak. Until then F10 and restart every few hours!

May I be honest without being misunderstood?

I'm starting to feel pressure to release this, but I want to be clear: I'm carrying KSPRC to EVE's new version, almost from scratch, because has a completely new way for the settings. That, now, include terrains... which is much more work, but much more possibilities too.

I'm using Kopernicus now, not RSS. I'm trying to support as much as I can the new EVE and Scatterer mods, and I want to include both in the new version of KSPRC, as soon as they become enough mature.

I've done reflections for several parts, which will be optionals. That include some engines. I'm doing new textures, new (graphic and sound) effects, new features, new illustrations and so on... I'm improving all the mod, a lot.

And I'm just one. But I love the fact of being just one. I do this for my fun and my love to the game. And I just share the result because I think the people could enjoy it.

But I do it when (and because) I think is enough good (and I have a pretty high standard for it).

So, I'll not do more hype until I finish (that includes EVE and Scatterer being ready). Because I want to enjoy the ride (please, let me do it).

Please, be patient. The more I enjoy the process, the more you'll enjoy the mod. It's a promise.
